cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a relay selection protocol for multi-hop networks, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the throughput and delay analysis of the protocol, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The protocol involves multiple nodes working together to achieve a common goal, which can be seen as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The protocol involves controlling the transmission of nodes to avoid interference, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of the protocol in terms of throughput and delay, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation.
